The acreage features mature timber stands with strong commercial value, rolling terrain ideal for wildlife management, and the size necessary for serious hunting operations. At 160 acres, the property provides sufficient scale for establishing food plots, creating sanctuary areas, and implementing comprehensive habitat improvements. The land's natural features support robust populations of whitetail deer, turkey, and small game. Beyond recreational use, this property offers flexibility for timber investment, potential development opportunities given its SR 26 frontage, or simply holding as a legacy asset. Properties of this size with paved road access are increasingly rare in Washington County, making this a noteworthy opportunity for investors, serious hunters, or those seeking a significant land holding in southeast Ohio. The combination of size, location, and natural resources makes this 160-acre tract a standout offering in the current market.

The property's location in Wood County provides a good balance of remoteness and accessibility to larger towns and amenities. Whether you're looking to establish a family hunting tradition, create a private getaway, or invest in West Virginia timberland, this 25-acre parcel offers excellent value and versatility. The property is ready for your vision - from simple recreational use to more developed improvements.

listings.title: 49 Acres in Washington County, Ohio - Zion Road
listings.shortDescription: This 49-acre Washington County property features a premier hilltop build site with panoramic views of lush ridges and deep ravines, ideal for your dream cabin. Directly bordering the Wayne National Forest, this mostly wooded tract offers exceptional hunting for deer and turkey along with an established trail system for easy exploration.
listings.overview: If you have been searching for the ultimate escape to the great outdoors, this 49-acre Washington County tract is the opportunity you've been waiting for. Priced at $220,900, this property offers a rare combination of absolute privacy, rugged natural beauty, and direct access to public land. Key Highlights of Tract 19: The Perfect Build Site: Perched at an elevation of over 1,000 feet, the premier hilltop site offers breathtaking panoramic views of high ridges and deep ravines—the perfect backdrop for a secluded log cabin or weekend retreat. A Hunter's Paradise: Bordering the Wayne National Forest directly on its eastern boundary, this land provides a seamless transition into thousands of acres of additional territory. The "big woods" habitat is teeming with whitetail deer, turkey, and small game. Ready to Explore: With 3,144 feet of frontage on a paved road and an established trail system winding through the older timber, the property is remarkably accessible for hiking, ATV riding, or reaching your favorite hunting blind. Whether you are looking to invest in timber, establish a basecamp for your outdoor adventures, or build a legacy home in the Frontier Local School District, Zion Ridge Tract 19 is a versatile canvas ready for your vision.

listings.title: Brooks Rd Lot 1 - 128 Acres in Washington County, OH
listings.shortDescription: Exceptional 128-acre woodland retreat in Washington County offering ultimate privacy off a quiet gravel road. Bordering Wayne National Forest with direct access to trophy muskie fishing on the Little Muskingum River, this is a true outdoorsman's paradise.
listings.overview: Own 128 acres of pristine Appalachian wilderness in Washington County, Ohio. Tucked away off a quiet gravel road in Lawrence Township, this property delivers the kind of seclusion most landowners only dream of—minimal road traffic and neighbors few and far between. The location transforms this from a simple land purchase into a gateway for endless outdoor adventures. With direct access to hundreds of acres of Wayne National Forest, you'll enjoy unlimited hiking, exploring, and wildlife observation right from your doorstep. The nearby Little Muskingum River is renowned for trophy muskie and exceptional smallmouth bass fishing. Hunters will find abundant whitetail deer, wild turkey, and small game throughout the heavily wooded terrain, with vast surrounding public lands extending your hunting grounds exponentially. Whether you envision building a secluded cabin retreat, establishing a family hunting camp, or preserving your own piece of wilderness, this property delivers on every front.

listings.title: Brooks Rd Lot 3 - 34 Acres in Washington County, OH

listings.overview: Discover the perfect canvas for your private retreat—34 acres of secluded woodland in Washington County, Ohio. This remarkable property offers an outstanding combination of size, location, and natural beauty for those seeking their own escape from everyday life. The land features an extensive network of trails and roads throughout the acreage, providing easy access to every corner from day one. Previous owners completed a select timber harvest, resulting in a well-managed woodland that promotes healthy forest growth while maintaining the natural character of the landscape—ready for your enjoyment without extensive initial work. Bordering Wayne National Forest instantly expands your recreational options to include hundreds of acres of public land for hiking, exploring, and hunting. The surrounding area is a true hunting paradise teeming with whitetail deer, wild turkey, and abundant small game. The remote setting off a quiet gravel road ensures minimal disturbance, creating an ideal environment for wildlife observation and outdoor pursuits.
